	<title>In Event Monitor display, event time always displayed</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Build ID: actf-accprobe-n200801141505-win32-incubation</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Steps To Reproduce:</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">In the Event Monitor display, the event time is always displayed regardless of whether it has been chosen.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">1 In the Event Monitor tool bar, select menu.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">2 In the pulldown menu, select "Choose columns to display...".</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.3">3 In the "Choose Table Columns" dialog, uncheck "Event Time".</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.4">4 In the Event Monitor tool bar, select "Start capture of events".</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.5">5 Move the cursor aound the desktop window to generate events.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Note the event time is displayed under another heading.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
